-- Mriya Plans to Invest Up to $250 Million, Interfax Says
-- B y   K a t e r y n a   C h o u r s i n a
-- 2012-04-13T12:54:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-13/mriya-plans-to-invest-up-to-250-million-interfax-says.html
Mriya Agro Holding Plc, a Ukrainian
agriculture company, plans to invest $100 million to $250
million to expand,  Interfax-Ukraine  reported, citing Larysa
Potsiluyko, head of accounting.  Mriya will increase agricultural lands in use by 20,000
hectares (49,400 acres) to 50,000 hectares and invest in
elevators in the Khmelnytskyi and Ternopil regions, the newswire
said. The company also plans to purchase additional agricultural
equipment, the Kiev-based news service reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kateryna Choursina in Kiev at 
